</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[212,1172,1380,1539]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">
Native to the Mediterranean Sea, this mussel now shows a worldwide distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Westfall KM &amp; Gardner J" box="[219,540,1451,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" pagination="898 - 909" refId="ref14122" refString="Westfall KM, Gardner J. 2010. Genetic diversity of Southern hemisphere blue mussels (Bivalvia: Mytilidae) and the identification of non-indigenous taxa. Biol J Linn Soc. 101: 898 - 909." type="journal article" year="2010">Westfall and Gardner 2010</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[604,667,1451,1475]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">Chile</collectingCountry>
, it was recorded for the first time in 2000 (
<bibRefCitation author="Daguin C &amp; Borsa P" box="[219,485,1483,1507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" pagination="389 - 397" refId="ref9849" refString="Daguin C, Borsa P. 2000. Genetic relationships of Mytilus galloprovincialis Lmk. populations worldwide: evidence from nuclear-DNA markers. In: Crame A, Harper E, Taylor J, editors. Bivalve systematics and evolution, Vol. 177. London: Geological Society of London Special Publications; p. 389 - 397." type="book chapter" year="2000">Daguin and Borsa 2000</bibRefCitation>
), and it has been recorded from Dichato (
<geoCoordinate box="[955,1048,1483,1507]" degrees="36" direction="south" minutes="33" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" precision="925" value="-36.55">
36°33 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1020,1026,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1060,1164,1483,1507]" degrees="72" direction="west" minutes="56" orientation="longitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" precision="925" value="-72.933334">
72°56 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1124,1130,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
) to Punta Arenas (
<geoCoordinate box="[415,510,1515,1539]" degrees="53" direction="south" minutes="10" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" precision="925" value="-53.166668">
53°10 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[480,486,1515,1539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[525,630,1515,1539]" degrees="70" direction="west" minutes="56" orientation="longitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" precision="925" value="-70.933334">
70°56 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[589,595,1515,1539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Tarifeno E &amp; Galleguillos R &amp; Rivera A &amp; Arriagada D &amp; Ferrada S &amp; Aguirre CB &amp; Seguel M" box="[654,880,1515,1539]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" pagination="167 - 172" refId="ref13867" refString="Tarifeno E, Galleguillos R, Llanos- Rivera A, Arriagada D, Ferrada S, Canales- Aguirre CB, Seguel M. 2012. Erroneous identification of the mussel, Mytilus galloprovincialis (Lamarck 1819) as the species Mytilus chilensis (Hupe, 1854) in the Bay of Concepcion, Chile. Gayana. 76: 167 - 172." type="journal article" year="2012">Tarifeño et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[212,1171,1595,1691]" box="[212,681,1595,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733">
<heading box="[212,681,1595,1619]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="1733" reason="5">
